Up to 100 Islamic teachers could be banned from working in schools for life following an investigation into their links to the Trojan Horse scandal .
It is understood a teaching watchdog is working on possible disciplinary cases against current and former staff members at some schools in Birmingham where extremist Islamic views were being forced on pupils .
This includes allegations an al-Qaeda style video featuring masked gunmen was copied in a classroom and teachers punished pupils by making them kneel on tiles .
More than 50 teachers - called the Park View Brotherhood - also alleged exchanged as many as 3,000 messages in a WhatsApp group which included British soldiers and claimed the murder of soldier Lee Rigby was a hoax .